title: Google Calendar event duplication
text: I could give this app a better review but it has a severe problem.   When an event (like recurring doctor or haircut appointments) is duplicated, the notifications revert to default instead of duplicating custom ones I set for that event.  I have to adjust them every time I duly event.  It’s painful.

title: Quick & Kind
text: Ariel fixed my necklace in less than 24 hrs. with exceptional service and kindness!!! I wish I had known about his shop sooner, but now that I know I will definitely go back for my jewelry needs. DJP Diamonds are a sweet gift!!

title: Great place for a Girls night… ANY NIGHT
text: Had the MOST amazing time for a girls night. We ordered EVERYTHING. Arancini of the moment, Bruschetta, wings, grilled shrimp, cauliflower bites, empanadas, ect. We were obsessed with it all. The service was personal, the atmosphere was amazing, they made us feel so welcome from the moment we walked in. ASK FOR BRIAN. He made our night! Funny to boot, and very knowledgeable of food and wine menu.

title: Follow up.
text:
Hi Google.
It’s Elijah. Thank you team Google for granting me access to so much knowledge. For creating and storing my passwords. Mostly though, thank you for allowing me to be a grumpy human at times and for not returning the similar treatment. I promise I’m getting better everyday.

Love you.

Elijah.

title: Arbor Pack And Mail
text: I can’t say enough about the service Sam provided in getting a mounted poster sent to my granddaughter in London. It was a family treasure that we wanted her to have but were frustrated by rejections . Until I took it to Arbor Pack and Mail. It arrived at her home in London within ten days and in perfect condition. We are all grateful for this caring service.
